sbol:ComponentDefinition.addgene:modificationsToBackbone: The pND-Ub vector is based on a modified pZE21 vector, contacting the pLtetO-1. cDNAs were amplified by polymerase chain reaction (PCR), digested and sub-cloned into the vectors. The mouse cDNA of the nDHFR fragment (residues 1-108) was PCR-amplified and sub-cloned between the KpnI and PacI sites (the PacI site was inserted into the vector by PCR) into the pZE21 vector. Then a flexible linker (Figure 4) was constructed a using two-step PCR method and digested with PacI and NotI (the NotI site was inserted into the vector by PCR) and cloned into the vector downstream to the pLtetO1-nDHFR. Ubiquitylation apparatus cassettes containing a His6-Ub-E2-E1 were PCR-amplified from pGEN plasmids expressing different E2s or Ub mutants (Keren-Kaplan et al, 2011) and sub-cloned as fusion to the C-terminus of the nDHFR-linker1 into the NotI and AvrII endonuclease recognition sites.
